{
  "texts": [
    "This paves the way towards creating standard resources that enhance the replicability of research across languages.",
    "ConclusionWe have described the methods to create the CT-EBM-SP corpus, a collection of 1200 texts about clinical trials studies and announcements in Spanish.",
    "This is the first resource for medical natural language processing of clinical trials in this language.",
    "Three experts have annotated it with entities from the Unified Medical Language System ® semantic groups (ANAT, CHEM, DISO and PROC).",
    "A 10% of the corpus was doubly annotated and a high inter-annotator agreement was achieved (average F1 = 85.65% ±4.79, strict match; 93.94% ±3.31, relaxed match)."
  ]
}